data.title: Mr. Abdellatif Ouahbi MP
data.text:
A lawyer by profession, Abedllatif Ouahbi has been working for the Moroccan Institute for Human Rights and is a founding member of the Moroccan branch of Amnesty International. Amongst others, he also worked as a counselor for the Center of Immigration Law in the Ministry of Human Rights and served as Vice-President for the Arab Organization of Young Lawyers.

He was elected Member of Parliament in 2011 and is currently serving as President of the Committee on Justice, Legislation and Human Rights in the Moroccan House of Representatives.
